HEADWORD: ingratiatory
<hw>ingratiatory</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>pleasingly
persuasive or intended to persuade; <as>as, her manner is quiet and
<ex>ingratiatory</ex> and a little too agreeable</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> coaxing.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>calculated to please or gain favor; same as
<er>ingratiating</er>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ingratiating.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ingratitude</ent>⟦br⟧
